03901nam a22006255i 9780292772267DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20211980txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927722677 a10.7560/7243032doi  a(DE-B1597)587812  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 4aGR177.T8F34 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04a3941 aFalassi, Alessandro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFolklore by the Fireside :bText and Context of the Tuscan Veglia /cAlessandro Falassi. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©1980  a1 online resource (400 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- t1 The World by the Fireplace -- t2 Fairy Tales for the Young and the Old "Oh, Listen to Me, Now. Once upon a Time . . ." -- t3 Bedtime and Children's Folklore "The Angel by the Bedside" -- t4 Courting in the Evening "If You Want to Woo, Bring Along a Chair" -- t5 The End of the Veglia The Right to Ask and the Obligation to Refuse" -- t6 The Veglia Dance "Dance Too, Adonis, Since Everyone Is Dancing" -- t7 The Outcasts' Counter- Veglia "Women, the Tavern, the Dice" -- t8 Conclusions -- tAppendix of Italian Texts -- tNotes -- tSelected Bibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFor centuries, social life in rural Tuscany has centered around the veglia, an evening gathering of family and friends at the hearth. Folklore by the Fireside is a thorough and insightful study of this custom—from the tales, riddles, lullabies, and folk prayers performed as the small children are put to bed to the courtship songs and dances later in the evening to the anti-veglia male gossip, card games, and protest songs originating in the tavern. Alessandro Falassi skillfully correlates the veglia to the rites of passage and family values of an agrarian society. Although the impact of mass media and other factors has tended to weaken the tradition, even today Tuscan children are taught to behave and adolescents are guided along the conventional path to adulthood, courtship, and marriage through veglia folklore. This is the first work to deal systematically with Tuscan folklore from a semiotic and structural viewpoint and to examine the veglia as a means of handing down traditional values. It is important not only for its careful, detailed description but also for its rigorous methodology and theoretical richness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAbrahams, Roger D.1 aAbrahams, Roger D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72430340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292772267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292772267/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK